  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel lengths off your<strong> courgette[s]</strong> with a peeler until you end up with a pile of courgette ribbons</p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>inner</strong> <strong>courgette stem[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>into bite-sized chunks</p><p>Chop your<strong> tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-and-red-pesto-orzo-with-courgette-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>courgette</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomato[es]</strong> and cook for 4-5 min further or until tender</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-and-red-pesto-orzo-with-courgette-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetables are softening, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[650ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-and-red-pesto-orzo-with-courgette-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes are tender, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> orzo </strong>and<strong> stock </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for an initial 12-15 min or until almost cooked through</p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to prevent it from sticking!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-and-red-pesto-orzo-with-courgette-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the orzo is almost cooked, stir through <strong>half</strong> your <strong>sun-dried tomato pesto</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-and-red-pesto-orzo-with-courgette-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>haddock bites</strong> to the pan, increase the heat to medium and cook, covered, for a further 4-5 min or until the haddock is cooked through and the orzo is tender – this is your <strong>haddock & red pesto orzo</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-and-red-pesto-orzo-with-courgette-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Combine the<strong> salad</strong> and <strong>courgette ribbons</strong> in a bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil </strong>and your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, then give everything a gentle mix up<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>courgette salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-and-red-pesto-orzo-with-courgette-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>haddock &</strong> <strong>red pesto orzo</strong> with the<strong> courgette salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>remaining pesto</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
